"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-01-19-transfer-olympic-lyon-complete-orban-signing\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Ligue 1 club, Olympic Lyon have announced the signing of Gift Orban for \\u20ac12m, DAILY POST reports.  The Nigerian joined the former Ligue 1 champions from Belgian Pro League outfit, KAA Gent.  Orban signed a contract until June 30, 2028.  The 21-year-old spent one-and-a-half seasons with Gent.  The powerful striker linked up with the Buffalos from Norwegian second division club, Stabaek in January 2023.  Orban scored 20 goals in 22 appearances across all competitions for Gent in the second half of last season.  He is the first Nigerian to sign for Olympic Lyon  Remo Stars defender, Ali joins Portuguese club, Feirense  EPL: Man City will be relegated if found guilty of 115 financial charges - Borson  Transfer: Griezmann leaves Atletico Madrid for Orlando City  Transfer: Club Brugge plot move for Fernandez  Transfer: Premier League clubs interested in Nigerian-born goalkeeper  Transfer: Rangers line up summer move for Sanusi  Transfer: Nwabali not concerned over free agent status  Transfer: Onazi moves to Lithuanian club FK Babrungas  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"